---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<style>
  .project-header {
    margin: 0;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .page__title {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    width: 100%;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .section__container {
    margin: 40px auto 80px;
    max-width: 820px;
  }
  
  .section__title {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .section__intro {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 8px 0 8px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #444;
  }

  .section__subtitle {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .section__list {
    margin: 16px 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
}

.section__list.--parent {
    background-color: #fff7ed;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px 40px;
    border: 1px solid #f3e2c7;
  }
  
  .section__item {
    margin: 6px 0;
    list-style: disc;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ✨ subtle section separation */
  .section__container + .section__container {
    border-top: 1px solid #eee;
    padding-top: 40px;
  }

  /* ✨ improve readability for dense content */
  p {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ✨ better code block spacing */
  pre {
    margin: 16px 0;
    padding: 12px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: #111;
    color: #eee;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  background: #0f172a; /* dark background */
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
}

thead {
  background: #1e293b;
}

th {
  text-align: left;
  padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: #e2e8f0;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

td {
  padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
  color: #cbd5f5;
  border-top: 1px solid #1e293b;
}

tbody tr {
  transition: background 0.2s ease;
}

tbody tr:hover {
  background: #1e293b;
}

/* Optional: highlight improvement (After column) */
td:last-child {
  color: #22c55e; /* subtle green */
  font-weight: 500;
}

/* Responsive */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  table {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  th, td {
    padding: 0.7rem;
  }
}
</style>

<Layout> 
      <div
    class="relative z-50 col-start-2 col-span-10 max-sm:col-start-3 max-sm:col-span-9"
  >
    <header class="project-header">
      <h1 class="page__title">Wildlife Rescue & Operations Platform</h1>
      <p class="page__subtitle">Solutions Engineering & System Design</p>

    </header>
<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">1. Problem & Goals</h2>
  <p class="section__intro">Campaign page creation was a manual, cross-team process that led to inefficiencies, delays, and inconsistent data.</p>

  <ul class="section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Campaign page creation relied on manual coordination between sales, frontend, and announcements teams</li>
    <li class="section__item">Workflow was fragmented:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Communication via chat tools (Chatwork)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Manual extraction and rewriting into tickets</li>
        <li class="section__item">Manual duplication of templates and folders</li>
        <li class="section__item">Inconsistent and hard-to-track data</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li class="section__item">Impact:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">6–8 hours to prepare a single page</li>
        <li class="section__item">8–15 back-and-forth messages per project</li>
        <li class="section__item">Frequent inconsistencies and information loss</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li class="section__item">Goals:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Reduce manual coordination and repetitive work</li>
        <li class="section__item">Standardize input and data handling</li>
        <li class="section__item">Improve delivery speed</li>
        <li class="section__item">Scale from ~16 to 30+ projects/month</li>
        <li class="section__item">Maintain quality through controlled automation</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
  
<section class="section__container">
  <h3 class="section__subtitle">Before vs After</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Aspect</th>
        <th>Before</th>
        <th>After</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Setup time</td>
        <td>6–8h</td>
        <td>2–4h</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Communication</td>
        <td>8–15 messages</td>
        <td>Minimal</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Data consistency</td>
        <td>Low</td>
        <td>High</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">2. Context & Constraints</h2>
  <p class="section__intro">
    The solution operates within a cross-team, semi-technical environment and must respect both technical limitations and business realities.
  </p>

  <ul class="section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Environment:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Cross-functional workflow (Sales, Frontend, Design, Announcements)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Non-technical users providing input</li>
        <li class="section__item">Asynchronous collaboration across teams</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li class="section__item">Technical constraints:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">No direct AI access to internal systems</li>
        <li class="section__item">Script-based execution (no backend services)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Use of existing tools (Google Sheets, Drive, Gemini AI)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li class="section__item">Business constraints:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Frontend-driven ecosystem (Node.js preferred)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Small team (2 members)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Fast adoption with minimal disruption</li>
        <li class="section__item">Cost efficiency vs scaling headcount</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li class="section__item">Assumptions:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">AI can structure semi-structured input</li>
        <li class="section__item">Human validation is required before publishing</li>
        <li class="section__item">Structured data improves consistency and scalability</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h3 class="section__subtitle">System Context</h3>
  <img src="/images/pagegen_diagram_systemboundries.jpg" alt="System Context Diagram" />
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">3. Users & Requirements</h2>

  <ul class="section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Users:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Sales team (input campaign data)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Frontend engineers (generate and validate pages)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Announcements team (content and tracking)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li class="section__item">Functional requirements:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Accept unstructured or semi-structured input</li>
        <li class="section__item">Convert input into structured JSON</li>
        <li class="section__item">Classify project type and templates</li>
        <li class="section__item">Generate HTML from templates</li>
        <li class="section__item">Store and share data across systems</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li class="section__item">Non-functional requirements:
      <ul class="section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Maintainability (Node.js ecosystem)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Consistency (single source of truth)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Security (no direct AI execution)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Usability (non-technical input support)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Reliability (fallback without AI)</li>
        <li class="section__item">Scalability (increasing campaign volume)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">4. System Overview</h2>
  <p class="section__intro">
    The system is designed as an AI-assisted pipeline separating data structuring, execution, and validation.
  </p>

  <ul class="section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">AI processing (input structuring)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Script-based execution</li>
    <li class="section__item">Human validation</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">System Flow</h3>
  <ol class="section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Sales provides input (Google Sheets)</li>
    <li class="section__item">AI transforms data into structured JSON</li>
    <li class="section__item">JSON becomes the source of truth</li>
    <li class="section__item">CLI generates pages</li>
    <li class="section__item">Frontend validates output</li>
    <li class="section__item">Pages are deployed</li>
  </ol>

  <img src="/images/pagegen_diagram_flow.jpg" alt="System Flow Diagram" />
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">5. Architecture</h2>

  <ul class=" section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">AI Processing (Gemini)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Data Layer (JSON)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Automation Layer (Apps Script)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Storage (Sheets, Drive)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Output (HTML, Markdown)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Human Validation</li>
  </ul>

  <img src="/images/pagegen_diagram_c2.jpg" alt="C2 Architecture Diagram" />

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">Core Pipeline (Representative)</h3>
  <pre><code class="language-json">
  function processRow(sheet, row)&#123;
    const lock = LockService.getScriptLock();
    try &#123;
      lock.waitLock(5000);
      // simplified
    &#125; finally &#123;
      lock.releaseLock();
    &#125;
  &#125;</code></pre>
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">6. Data Model & Behavior</h2>

  <ul class="section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Project Management Data:
      <ul class=" section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Stored in Google Sheets</li>
        <li class="section__item">Contains campaign metadata and ownership</li>
        <li class="section__item">Tracks project lifecycle</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li class="section__item">Page Management Data:
      <ul class=" section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Stored in Google Sheets</li>
        <li class="section__item">Defines page configuration and tracking</li>
        <li class="section__item">Includes links, status, and delivery info</li>
      </ul>
    </li>

    <li class="section__item">Page Generation Data (Source of Truth):
      <ul class=" section__list">
        <li class="section__item">Structured JSON used for generation</li>
        <li class="section__item">Decouples content from implementation</li>
        <li class="section__item">Enables consistent and repeatable outputs</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <pre><code>&#123;
  "template": "store_osaka",
  "page_path": "osaka_store",
  "store": "osaka",
  "title": "Manga in Osaka store",
  "sales_period_start": "2026/03/01",
  "sales_period_end": "2026/05/30",
  "post_sales_allowed": true
  &#125;</code></pre>

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">CLI Prototype</h3>
  <pre><code>node src/generator.js --file shibuya.json</code></pre>
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">7. Decisions & Trade-offs</h2>

  <ul class=" section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">AI limited to structuring (reliability over flexibility)</li>
    <li class="section__item">JSON as source of truth (strict schema required)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Node.js ecosystem (simple and maintainable)</li>
    <li class="section__item">Human-in-the-loop validation</li>
    <li class="section__item">Apps Script simplicity vs scalability</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">8. Reliability & Scalability</h2>

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">Reliability</h3>
  <ul class=" section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Input validation</li>
    <li class="section__item">Script validation</li>
    <li class="section__item">Frontend review</li>
    <li class="section__item">Fallback without AI</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">Scalability</h3>
  <ul class=" section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Current: Sheets + scripts</li>
    <li class="section__item">Future: backend service + database + dashboard</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="section__container">
  <h2 class="section__title">9. Outcome & Learnings</h2>

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">Impact</h3>
  <ul class=" section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">6–10h → 2–4h preparation time</li>
    <li class="section__item">Reduced communication overhead</li>
    <li class="section__item">Scaled to 30+ projects/month</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">Outcome</h3>
  <ul class=" section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">Standardized workflow</li>
    <li class="section__item">Improved data consistency</li>
    <li class="section__item">Foundation for internal platform</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="section__subtitle">Learnings</h3>
  <ul class=" section__list --parent">
    <li class="section__item">AI works best for structuring, not execution</li>
    <li class="section__item">Workflow design improves team efficiency</li>
    <li class="section__item">Human validation increases reliability</li>
    <li class="section__item">Structured data enables scalability</li>
  </ul>
</section>
</Layout>
